The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Rituparno unwell
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Rituparno unwell
          A STAFF REPORTER                                    
	Rituparno Ghoshhas been taken ill and is undergoing treatment in a private clinic of south Calcutta. It is a case of long-term diabetes, early stage of pancreatitis and mild enlargement of the liver, consultant physician Rajib Seal, who is supervising the film-makers treatment, told Metro. Ghosh was admitted on Friday after a few days of illness and is expected to be under strict medical supervision this week.        
	Boy dead: Upendra Shaw, 10, who went missing from his Lokenath Bose Road home in Topsia on Friday evening, was found dead beside a building under construction on Topsia Road (East) on Saturday.        
	Fatal mishap: Kundan Roy, a Class VI student, was killed after being knocked down by a lorry at the Strand Road-Broja Gobindo Saha Lane crossing, in Jorabagan, on Saturday afternoon.        
	Lightning strike: Mohammed Karibul, 12, died reportedly after being struck by lightning at Barasat on Sunday evening.        
	Dysentry outbreak: About 140 residents of Dinendrapally near Kestopur, in ward number 28 of Rajarhat-Gopalpur Municipality, fell sick showing symptoms of dysentery on Sunday. Civic officials said a leak in a supply pipe might have contaminated the drinking water.                                                                                                                                                                                          
